Consider the following code. If an `ArithmeticException` occurs at the line marked 'POINT OF EXCEPTION', which catch block will handle it?

try {
    // Outer try block
    try {
        // Inner try block
        int result = 10 / 0; // POINT OF EXCEPTION
    } catch (NullPointerException e) {
        System.out.println("NullPointerException caught");
    }
} catch (ArithmeticException e) {
    System.out.println("ArithmeticException caught");
}

Analyze the code. What is printed to the console?

try {
    try {
        throw new ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException();
    } catch (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
        System.out.print("Inner Catch / ");
        throw new RuntimeException(e); // Re-throwing a wrapped exception
    } finally {
        System.out.print("Inner Finally / ");
    }
} catch (RuntimeException e) {
    System.out.print("Outer Catch / ");
} finally {
    System.out.print("Outer Finally");
}
